#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.47"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.47:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.47:0.2"
msgid "5. Muṇḍarājavagga "
msgstr "5. With King Muṇḍa "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: pañcadhanasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.47:0.3"
msgid "47. Dhanasutta "
msgstr "47. Wealth "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an5.47:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, dhanāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five kinds of wealth. "

msgctxt "an5.47:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an5.47:1.3"
msgid "Saddhādhanaṃ, sīladhanaṃ, sutadhanaṃ, cāgadhanaṃ, paññādhanaṃ. "
msgstr "The wealth of faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an5.47:2.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, saddhādhanaṃ? "
msgstr "And what is the wealth of faith? "

msgctxt "an5.47:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako saddho hoti, saddahati tathāgatassa bodhiṃ: "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple has faith in the Realized One’s awakening: "

msgctxt "an5.47:2.3"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti. "
msgstr "‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’ "

msgctxt "an5.47:2.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, saddhādhanaṃ. "
msgstr "This is called the wealth of faith. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an5.47:3.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, sīladhanaṃ? "
msgstr "And what is the wealth of ethics? "

msgctxt "an5.47:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti. "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or take alcoholic drinks that cause negligence. "

msgctxt "an5.47:3.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sīladhanaṃ. "
msgstr "This is called the wealth of ethics. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an5.47:4.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, sutadhanaṃ? "
msgstr "And what is the wealth of learning? "

msgctxt "an5.47:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako bahussuto hoti … pe … diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdho. "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple is very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s totally full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reciting them, mentally scrutinizing them, and comprehending them theoretically. "

msgctxt "an5.47:4.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sutadhanaṃ. "
msgstr "This is called the wealth of learning. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an5.47:5.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, cāgadhanaṃ? "
msgstr "And what is the wealth of generosity? "

#. VAR: vosaggarato → vossaggarato (s1-3, pts1, c1)
msgctxt "an5.47:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako vigatamalamaccherena cetasā agāraṃ ajjhāvasati muttacāgo payatapāṇi vosaggarato yācayogo dānasaṃvibhāgarato. "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple lives at home rid of the stain of stinginess, freely generous, open-handed, loving to let go, committed to charity, loving to give and to share. "

msgctxt "an5.47:5.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, cāgadhanaṃ. "
msgstr "This is called the wealth of generosity. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an5.47:6.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, paññādhanaṃ? "
msgstr "And what is the wealth of wisdom? "

msgctxt "an5.47:6.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako paññavā hoti, udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā. "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple is wise. They have the wisdom of arising and passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of suffering. "

msgctxt "an5.47:6.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, paññādhanaṃ. "
msgstr "This is called the wealth of wisdom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.47:6.4"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhanānīti. "
msgstr "These are the five kinds of wealth. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.54, sc7
msgctxt "an5.47:7.1"
msgid "Yassa saddhā tathāgate, "
msgstr "Whoever has faith in the Realized One, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.47:7.2"
msgid "acalā suppatiṭṭhitā; "
msgstr "unwavering and well grounded; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.47:7.3"
msgid "Sīlañca yassa kalyāṇaṃ, "
msgstr "whose ethical conduct is good, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.47:7.4"
msgid "ariyakantaṃ pasaṃsitaṃ. "
msgstr "praised and loved by the noble ones; "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an5.47:8.1"
msgid "Saṅghe pasādo yassatthi, "
msgstr "who has confidence in the Saṅgha, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.47:8.2"
msgid "ujubhūtañca dassanaṃ; "
msgstr "and correct view: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.47:8.3"
msgid "Adaliddoti taṃ āhu, "
msgstr "they’re said to be prosperous, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.47:8.4"
msgid "amoghaṃ tassa jīvitaṃ. "
msgstr "their life is not in vain. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an5.47:9.1"
msgid "Tasmā saddhañca sīlañca, "
msgstr "So let the wise devote themselves "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.47:9.2"
msgid "pasādaṃ dhammadassanaṃ; "
msgstr "to faith, ethical behavior, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.47:9.3"
msgid "Anuyuñjetha medhāvī, "
msgstr "confidence, and insight into the teaching, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.47:9.4"
msgid "saraṃ buddhāna sāsanan”ti. "
msgstr "remembering the instructions of the Buddhas.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.47:9.5"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
